    {
      "kind": "parameters",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A rendering context.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "ctx"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A pixel buffer object.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "pbuffer"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The cube map face to draw if the buffer texture target is type ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": "; otherwise pass ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "0",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "face"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The mipmap level to draw. This must not exceed the maximum mipmap level set when the pixel buffer object was created. Pass ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "0",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " for a texture target that does not support mipmaps.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "level"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A virtual screen value. The virtual screen determines the renderer that OpenGL uses to draw to the pixel buffer object. For best performance, for a pixel buffer used as a texture source, you should supply the a virtual screen value that results in using the same renderer used by the context that’s the texturing target.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "screen"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return-value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Returns ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GL_FALSE",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " if it fails for any reason, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GL_TRUE",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " otherwise. If an error occurs, call the function ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.agl/documentation/AGL/aglGetError",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to determine what the error is. See Discussion for more details.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The first time you call this function for a specific pixel buffer object, the system creates the necessary buffers. The buffers are created to support  the pixel formats used to create the rendering context. The storage requirements for pixel buffer objects, which can be quite large, are very similar to the requirements for windows or views with OpenGL contexts attached. All drawable objects compete for the same scarce resources. This function can fail is there is not enough contiguous VRAM for each buffer. It’s best to code defensively with a scheme that reduces resource consumption without causing the application to resort to failure. Unless, of course, failure is the only viable alternative.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ability to attach a pbuffer to a context is supported only on renderers that export ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GL_APPLE_pixel_buffer",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GL_EXTENSIONS",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " string. Before calling this function, you should programmatically determine if it’s possible to attach a pbuffer to a context by querying ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GL_EXTENSIONS",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " in the context and looking for ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GL_APPLE_pixel_buffer",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". If that extension is not present, the  renderer won’t allow setting the pbuffer. (In this case, the function correctly returns ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GL_FALSE",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", although the error returned by ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.agl/documentation/AGL/aglGetError",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " may be misleading.)",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In order of performance, these are the renderers you should consider using when setting up a rendering context to attach to a pbuffer:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "A hardware renderer.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The generic render, but only with an offscreen pixel format and ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "glTexSubImage",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ".",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The Apple software renderer, which supports pbuffers in macOS 10.4.8 and later.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
